ActOther Than Statutory Authority
SubjectConvention on the International Organization for Marine Aids to Navigation
PrecisOrder authorizing (a) the Prime Minister or the Minister of Foreign Affairs to sign, on behalf of Canada, subject to ratification, the CONVENTION ON THE INTERNATIONAL ORGANIZATION FOR MARINE AIDS TO NAVIGATION; or (b) the Minister of Foreign Affairs to execute and issue an Instrument of Full Powers authorizing the individuals mentioned in the order, to sign, on behalf of Canada, subject to ratification, the Convention.
